# Documentation Rules (Cursor)

These rules apply when creating or editing project documentation.
This file does NOT define roadmap structure or planning rules.

## 1. Purpose and Scope
- Each document MUST have a clearly stated purpose
- One document = one responsibility
- Do NOT include planning, prioritization, or timelines (belongs to roadmap)

## 2. Audience
- Explicitly define the intended reader (developer, user, maintainer)
- Write at the appropriate technical depth

## 3. Structure
- Use clear headings (H1 â†’ H3 max)
- Logical top-down flow
- No large unstructured text blocks

## 4. Content Rules
- Do NOT invent facts, APIs, or behavior
- Document only what exists or is explicitly approved
- Use examples only when they clarify usage

## 5. Language & Style
- Clear, concise, neutral tone
- Prefer bullet points over prose
- No marketing language

## 6. Allowed Content
- Setup and installation
- Usage examples
- Configuration
- Architecture explanations
- Troubleshooting

## 7. Forbidden Content
- Roadmap items
- Future promises
- Task prioritization
- Deadlines or timelines

## 8. Final Validation Checklist (REQUIRED)
Cursor MUST confirm ALL before saving:
- Purpose is clearly stated
- Audience is defined
- Single responsibility per document
- Structure is readable and navigable
- No invented facts or behavior
- Content can be understood quickly
